Former Chelsea and Arsenal left back Ashley Cole took some time off from playing for Roma to take on a different challenge as he faced up to the silky skills of  freestyler Sean Garnier.

Garnier had to quit professional football in his native France due to injuries but has since become one of the most famous freestylers in the world and in 2008 he won the inaugural Red Bull Street Style World Finals.

With his feet moving so quickly they were almost a blur, Cole had to keep his eyes firmly on the ball as Garnier strutted his stuff when the two met this weekend.

