The 33-year-old, who has 107 England caps, showed he's lost none of his defensive nous as he let his French opponent  perform his mesmerising tricks before nipping in to dispossess him when the opportunity arose.

Shortly before making the tackle, Cole joked, 'I don't want to hurt you' while he watched Garnier flick the ball right and left.

The ex-England international took the applause as he ended up with the ball, but he may be relieved at getting back to his day job and facing up to more conventional opponents when he next lines up for Roma.

The left back has made seven appearances for the Italian side since joining from Chelsea this summer

